social_posts.post_text:
We’re still unpacking here but at least I can finally start figuring out what I want to do with my studio room. 

It seems like it needs some Ichabod friendly seating.

Thanks for being patient with orders and emails! I’m working on them!

Thanks for all your support this year, we really appreciate it 🖤

Sagittarius season. ♐️

Keep moving, keep going. Eyes on the prize. 

#zodiac #sagittarius #sagittariusseason

Told myself I would work on this during the weekend but this is as far as I got. 

Got distracted by having fun with friends and decorating, it really is December, I guess. Worth it. 🖤

Hoping to print these on some rough linen cloths I’ve been hoarding. We’ll see how patient I am this week. 

#linoleum #printmaking #illustration

On Dec 21 at 5PST I’m going to be putting some Knight of Night prints and some printed cloths up on the shop. 

Of course, absolutely not going to get to you by Christmas. Depending on how the snow in Seattle is I may just start my planned break early, to be honest! 

If you’re cool with a little gift for yourself at the start of the year, I’m your pal.

For anyone waiting on calendars, I honestly ran out of ideas and wasn’t sure I’d be making one. I finally got something rolling around in my brain and I hope to have one ready to pop in the shop asap. I appreciate the very kind prodding 🖤

Have a wonderful solstice, all. Sip warm things and appreciate the excess darkness we’re blessed with tonight. 🌲💀

#wintersolstice

Here's my drawing of what I carved for my 2022 altar cloth, I'm glad I finished it because the sketch was bouncing around my procreate files for a while now and it kept haunting me. 

My favorite symbols on this one is probably a tie between the scorpion and the beet. It's hard to pin down, to be honest. 

#illustration #esoteric #altarcloth #symbolism #magic

Working on some secret things and for once trying to document the process. I find myself making things and never taking a picture before sending them out. It’s a bad habit, I’d like to have a better record of what I make! 

It’s too easy to judge what you do by what you can share, trying to calm that down and document for ME.

This summer you can find me at a show I’m really excited for, find me at @bloodofgodszine Annual Merrymaking. 

💀 Wine! Art! Zines! Metal! 💀

I’m hoping to drive with a car full of new work to sell and I hope to come back with a whole lot of wine and fun stories.

Finally got a makers mark so I can at least claim the things I make. I learned from this design (not fine enough, too much depression space for what I need it to do) but I’m very very excited about it. 

⚒️⚒️

Made a handful of earrings for the Annual Merrymaking that @bloodofgodszine is hosting in July. It feels good to have shows where you can make things that you love and not even have to have a hint of “what if people this this is weird.” 

Also, I know I’m a day late for #worldgothday but be sure I am always celebrating. You’re perfect, my fellow goths.

Look forward to more skulls, snakes, and monsters 🖤💀🖤

Did you know one of my favorite movies is Titus? The Julie Taymor one. 

I haven’t watched it in years and wanted to make something based on my strong memories of it.
🔪👨‍🍳🩸
I've been making work for me, realizing the joy that people get with fan art I wanted to make some of my own for my favorite films that have inspired me. This one is part of an Julie Taymor's Titus, a shockingly beautiful film of Shakespeare's famously gruesome play Titus Andronicus.

These are up in my shop now, as well as a few other brass pieces. Felt good to get back on the saddle with making fun things for me.

I really love getting hauls of old photos, I keep telling myself I’ll start the project I intended with them but in reality it’s just an excuse to remember people have always been complicated. We have always been the same, it’s comforting.

I tried my best: 

Dear Nettie:

Would this possibly answer your letter?
I am just terribly busy these days. Am helping my brother’s wife more and clean house. So please accept this for an answer and write again. Does this look like me? The others were better, but have run out of then, so — — this. What are you doing now days? Have you gone to many dances and the like Nettie? 

The things remain the same between Pearl and I. Haven’t had a word from her yet. And I swear I will never write again - unless she r—s and writes soon either. I can’t understand this! Her feeling the way she does.

Well, Best wishes
Love - Bess

-My address is now Lawn Hill, Iowa
